post_text:
JT School: Great News JT Families! The USDA is making breakfast and lunch free to all children through December 31, 2020, but is subject to end earlier due to available USDA funds. Breakfast and lunch will be available free every day to all students effective tomorrow. Because at the beginning of COVID we did not qualify for the program, we partnered with Claremore through the summer. We have now applied and been approved for this due to certain waivers.

We do encourage families who have not yet completed the 2020-2021 free and reduced lunch application to complete it should this program end. If you need another copy, please contact the school.

We started handing out last year’s yearbooks on the first day of school for those students that ordered and paid for them already. If you contacted Mrs Gray or the school after we were out of school, your students will be in their childs office ready to be paid for and picked up at the front desk. If your student was in 3rd grade last year it will be in the south campus office and if they were in 6th grade last year theirs will be in the jh office for payment and pick up. Also we have yearbooks still available if anyone would like to buy one after the first day of school. They will be available in each office at each building. They are $25.00 and can pay with cash or check.

For the 8th graders that graduated last year, if you have paid for a yearbook, you may pick them up in Mr Crum’s office. If anyone that wants to buy one, you can purchase one in the office.

shared_text:
Karen Lyons‎Justus-Tiawah School
July 22 at 9:27 AM ·

2020-21 7th and 8th Grade Math Parents
I am asking that each student have their own calculator.

For 7th grade ...just a plain ol' 4-function calculator. It is important that they do NOT have the +/- key.
I'd recommend the Dollar Store or even Dollar Tree.

For 8th grade we use a scientific calculator. TI 30s Multiview. These are usually available at Walmart, I also found them on amazon for same price.
I have put pictures for reference.
If you have any questions, please email me at
Klyons@justustiawah.com

Get started with Sora for 4th-8th graders at Justus-Tiawah School.
With Sora, you can get free ebooks and audiobooks from your school until June 30, 2020.
1. Install the Sora app from the Apple App Store or Google Play Store, or go to soraapp.com
2. In Sora, find your school by typing in the school code justustiawahok
3. Sign in with your school email and password.
4. Browse the Explore tab and borrow a book. Your book will open so you can start reading right away.
5. Close your book and go to your Shelf to see all your books. From there
you can:
Tap Open Book or Open Audiobook to read or listen to the book.
Tap Options to renew or return the book, get to your notes and highlights, and more.
If you have questions or need help, contact Jennifer Admire at jadmire@justustiawah.com
text:
Get started with Sora for 4th-8th graders at Justus-Tiawah School.
With Sora, you can get free ebooks and audiobooks from your school until June 30, 2020.
1. Install the Sora app from the Apple App Store or Google Play Store, or go to soraapp.com
2. In Sora, find your school by typing in the school code justustiawahok
3. Sign in with your school email and password.
4. Browse the Explore tab and borrow a book. Your book will open so you can start reading right away.
5. Close your book and go to your Shelf to see all your books. From there
you can:
Tap Open Book or Open Audiobook to read or listen to the book.
Tap Options to renew or return the book, get to your notes and highlights, and more.
If you have questions or need help, contact Jennifer Admire at jadmire@justustiawah.com

Makinzee Joslin- 1st alternate trumpet-7th grade band
Robert McDaniel- 2nd alternate trombone-7th grade band

Damon Means- 1st chair trumpet- 7th grade band
Allison Mooney- 3rd chair tenor saxophone- 7the grade band.

Congratulations to these fine musicians!

Back row: Makinzee Joslin, Robert McDaniel, Sarah Joslin, Jessica Lavigne, Henry Thompson.
Front row: Campbell Crum, Damon Means
Not pictured: Allison Mooney

The drive will last until Thursday, November 21st at 10am. The homeroom that collects the most cans will receive a pizza party.

post_text:
Join us for an "Incredible" Outdoor Movie Night to benefit the "Incredible" Cory Tyre!

Cory will be a 3rd grader at Justus-Tiawah and has recently been diagnosed with Burkitt's Lymphoma. He is responding to treatments, but has a long road ahead. All proceeds from the event will go towards Cory's medical and travel expenses.

We will be showing Incredibles 2 on August 3rd at the North Campus. Approximate start time will be 9:10 PM (or dark). Event will be held indoors if there is inclement weather. Admission will be $3 and concessions will be available.

Bring lawn chairs or blankets for your viewing comfort and be prepared for a fun evening under the stars!

post_text: Have you ever considered how our brains, mouths, tongue, and teeth all work together to make speaking possible? What if something doesn't work - Can it be corrected? post_text:
Justus-Tiawah Early Enrollment
New Pre-K or new Kindergarten students that plan to attend Justus-Tiawah School in the fall may come by the North Campus Elementary office to pick up an enrollment packet on March 6, 7, or 8 from 9:00-2:30. Return the completed forms on March 12 or 14 from 10:00-12:00 or 1:00-2:00. Also bring student’s birth certificate, certificate of degree of Indian blood (CDIB card), proof of residency, and current immunization record. Students will not be placed in a class until all paperwork has been received. For those interested in having a tour of the elementary, tours will be given on March 29 at 10:00 am. If you have questions, please call the Elementary office at 918-341-3626.
